def fibonacci(n):
    if n <= 1:
        return n
    else:
        return fibonacci(n-1) + fibonacci(n-2)
```

This function uses recursion to calculate the nth Fibonacci number. The base cases are when `n` is 0 or 1, in which case it simply returns `n`. For all other values of `n`, it calls itself with `n-1` and `n-2`, adding the results together to get the nth Fibonacci number.

